C++ emOwnPtr.h: unique-ownership smart pointer (pre-C++11 unique_ptr).

Superseded by Rust's ownership model:
  emOwnPtr<T>      -> Option<Box<T>>
  emOwnArrayPtr<T> -> Vec<T>
  Set/Reset         -> = Some(...) / = None (Drop runs automatically)
  Release           -> .take()
  Get               -> .as_ref()

The deleter infrastructure (emOwnPtrBase, emOwnPtrDeleter, emOwnArrayPtrDeleter)
has no Rust equivalent because Drop handles deallocation natively.

17 files outside emCore use this type. All map to the same Option<Box<T>>
pattern — no app-specific concerns.
